an change in the region, it also engages with a number of key current areas of debate, including: the nature and direction of the agrarian transition in Asia, and its distinctiveness vis à vis transitions in the global North; the persistence of the smallholder notwithstanding deep and rapid structural change; and the question of the efficiency and productivity of smallholder-based farming set against concerns over global and national food security.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAsian Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aEconomics. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 4aSouth East Asia. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Agribusiness.2bisacsh  aAsia, Smallholder, Agrarian change.1 aAndriesse, Edo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnh, Nguyen Tuan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillen, Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillen, Jamie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHisyam Kamarudin, Khairul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHung, Po-Yi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNgah, Ibrahim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeou, Chivoin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRigg, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRigg, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShoji, Gen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoukkhy, Outhai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, Eric C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.go